On Education and Sharing Day, President Biden honors the memory of Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson, also known as the Lubavitcher Rebbe. The Rebbe dedicated his life to outreach and teaching, emphasizing the importance of education, tolerance, and learning. Despite experiencing the horrors of World War II, he believed that education could combat hate and contribute to the betterment of society. From Brooklyn, he established schools and institutions aimed at helping individuals reach their full potential. The Rebbe advocated for compassion, justice, and character-building in education. President Biden reaffirms his administration's commitment to defending the values championed by the Rebbe, such as equality, dignity, and respect for all. He emphasizes the importance of stamping out intolerance and ensuring that every child has access to education. President Biden encourages everyone to translate pain into action and tears into growth, emphasizing the role of education in shaping the future of America. He proclaims April 2, 2023, as Education and Sharing Day and calls upon individuals and institutions across the United States to observe this day with appropriate programs and activities.